content: Just landed in NYC. The skyline never fails to make my heart skip a beat. First stop: meet with my mentor to discuss career moves.
Caught up with old friends from NYU. Over coffee, pitched my AI urban planning project. They loved the idea, suggested some potential investors.
Scheduled a meeting with the quant firm. Going to pitch a strategy based on the ethical trading principles I reflected on during my travels.
The pitch went surprisingly well! They're interested but want a detailed proposal. Time to put the pen to paper... or the code to screen.
Working late nights on the AI urban planning project. It's coming along, but integrating real-time data is proving challenging.
Had a breakthrough with the data integration. The project is starting to look like something I can actually present.
Reconnected with a former classmate now working in neural interface tech. He's agreed to mentor me in understanding cognitive enhancement.
First lesson in neural interfaces was mind-blowing. Literally. Trying to wrap my head around how this could revolutionize trading strategies.
Met with potential investors for the AI project. They're intrigued but want more on how it addresses privacy concerns. Back to the drawing board.
Finally, a proposal ready for the quant firm. Submitted it today. Now, the waiting game begins.
The quant firm got back to me. They want a second meeting to discuss specifics. This could be it!
Revamped the privacy protection features in my AI project. It's stronger now, but still needs fine-tuning.
Turned 22 today. Reflecting on the past year, I see how much I've grown. This project feels like a culmination of my experiences.
Met with the quant firm again. They offered me a position on their team, but it's not quite what I was hoping for. Negotiating for a better fit.
The AI project is almost ready for a soft launch. Planning a small event to showcase it to friends and potential partners.
Setback: The quant firm can't offer the role I wanted. But, they're interested in my AI project for potential future collaboration. Silver lining?
The AI urban planning project soft launch was a hit! Got some valuable feedback, and now, it's time to refine and scale up.
Just wrapped up a two-day negotiation with the quant firm. They're considering a tailored role for me. Now, I'm studying up on the latest in cognitive enhancement to bring something new to the table.
Had an enlightening session with my mentor. He opened my eyes to the ethical implications of cognitive tech in trading. Time to integrate this into my proposal for the quant firm.
Revised the AI urban planning project based on feedback. Set a date for the pilot in a small urban area. Now, I just need to iron out the last bugs and secure funding.
The quant firm meeting went well. They're intrigued by the cognitive enhancement angle, but they want a demo. Planning a prototype presentation for next week.
Spent the last few days refining the AI urban planning project's real-time data integration. It's nearly there, but I'm worried about the scalability.
Demo for the quant firm was a success! They're ready to move forward with a contract. Now, I'm preparing for the pilot launch of the urban planning project.
Pilot launch date set for the AI project! Spent the weekend with friends brainstorming how to make the launch event memorable. It's more than just work now; it's a community effort.
Signed the contract with the quant firm. It's official, but the role still needs some tweaks. Meanwhile, I'm deep into AI ethics discussions with new contacts from a conference.
The urban planning project is ready for its pilot. The team and I are putting the final touches. Also, had a coffee chat with a privacy expert. This could really shape my AI work.
Just had the most awkward moment trying to explain my project to a potential investor. I accidentally called my AI 'my baby'. He laughed, but I'm not sure if that's good or bad.
The pilot launch was a rollercoaster of emotions. It had some hiccups, but the community feedback was overwhelmingly positive. Now, refining based on real-world data.
